Ogre municipality (Latvian: Ogres novads) is a municipality in Vidzeme, Latvia. The municipality was formed in 2002 by merging Ogre town and Ogresgals parish. In 2009 it absorbed Krape parish, eipene parish, Laubere parish, Madliena parish, Mazozoli parish, Meele parish, Suntai parish and Taurupe parish the administrative centre being Ogre. 
